.TH "rpc_peeraddr" 9 "rpc_peeraddr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rpc_peeraddr \- extract remote peer address from clnt's xprt
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "size_t" rpc_peeraddr
.BI "(struct rpc_clnt *clnt "  ","
.BI "struct sockaddr *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t bufsize "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "clnt" 12
RPC client structure
.IP "buf" 12
target buffer
.IP "bufsize" 12
length of target buffer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns the number of bytes that are actually in the stored address.
